3. RedisSearch (Managed Redis Enterprise on Azure)

Why RedisSearch

ğŸš€ Ultra-low latency â€” sub-millisecond text and vector queries.

ğŸ”¡ Full-text search supports fuzzy, prefix, and phonetic matching (via PHONETIC dm:en).

ğŸ§± Can store compact phonetic keys or embeddings alongside structured metadata.

ğŸ’¡ Ideal for shared caches or smaller datasets (< hundreds of millions).


Limitations

Limited scoring customization.

Less mature synonym management than Elasticsearch/Solr.



